==Compositions==
Paul was also a prolific composer. Some of the songs he wrote were "[[Song in Blue]]", "Cryin{{'"}}, "Hip-Billy Boogie", "[[Suspicion (Les Paul song)|Suspicion]]", "[[Mandolino (Les Paul instrumental)|Mandolino]]", "Magic Melody", "[[Don'cha Hear Them Bells]]", "[[The Kangaroo (song)|The Kangaroo]]", "Big-Eyed Gal", "Deep in the Blues", "All I Need is You", "Take a Warning", "Mammy's Boogie", "Up And At 'Em", "Pacific Breeze", "Golden Sands", "Hawaiian Charms", "Mountain Railroad", "Move Along, Baby (Don't Waste My Time)", "Dry My Tears", "I Don't Want You No More", "Doing the Town", "Les' Blues",<ref>Paul, Les. ''The Guitar Magic of Les Paul''. 10 original guitar solos with piano and 2nd guitar accompaniment. Leeds Music Corporation, New York, 1947.</ref> "No Strings Attached", "Subterfuge", "Lament For Strings", "Five Alarm Fire", "You Can't Be Fit as a Fiddle (When You're Tight as a Drum)", and "Walkin' and Whistlin' Blues".

